  <definitions>
    <item>
      <id>1</id>
      <text>A molecular entity (and the corresponding chemical species) that is an electron-pair acceptor and therefore able to react with a Lewis base to form a Lewis adduct, by sharing the electron pair furnished by the Lewis base. For example: [image: Not defined]</text>
